               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17510417-18-off93-c144" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-18-defend183 t17510417-18-off93 t17510417-18-verdict95"></join>
         
               <p>279. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17510417-18-defend183" type="defendantName">
                     Elizabeth 
                     Paxton 
                  <interp inst="t17510417-18-defend183" type="surname" value="Paxton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-defend183" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-defend183" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17510417-18-off93" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-off93" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-off93" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one cloth coat, value 15 s. one cloth waistcoat, value 10 s. one silk handkerchief, one linen handkerchief, and seven iron keys
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17510417-18-victim185" type="victimName">
                     Charles 
                     Peirce 
                  <interp inst="t17510417-18-victim185" type="surname" value="Peirce"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-victim185" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-victim185" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-18-off93 t17510417-18-victim185"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17510417-18-cd94" type="crimeDate">March 14</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17510417-18-off93 t17510417-18-cd94"></join>. *</p>
               <p>Charles Peirce. On the 14th of March this coat and waistcoat with the other things in the pockets, were hanging upon the banisters or behind the door; a neighbour that lives a-cross the street told me, she saw the prisoner at the bar go out at my door with the coat and waistcoat she was taken up the Saturday following at a pawn broker's offering to pawn one of the handker chiefs, the handkerchiefs produced in court with the letter P. upon it and deposed to: she was carried to the round house, there she delivered to me my keys and the other handkerchiefs, saying she took them all out of my house, and she told me she sold the coat and waistcoat to Jobb Holt who keeps a gin shop for a guinea, we went and searched the house and found them, produced in court with the other things and deposed to.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17510417-18-person186">
                  Thomas 
                  Rutherford 
               <interp inst="t17510417-18-person186" type="surname" value="Rutherford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-person186" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-person186" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , the constable, confirmed the above, <rs id="t17510417-18-verdict95" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17510417-18-verdict95" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
